00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:13.000
The R1 has a hot cue feature which is similar to that found on the CDJ-2000nexus. The hot cues allow you to jump to any point in the track without interrupting playback.

00:00:14.000 --> 00:00:22.000
You’ve got a hot cue section on each deck and to use it make sure you’re in hot cue mode and then when a track’s playing just press A B or C.

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:39.000
When they’re recorded the buttons will light up.  I’ve recorded a kick, a high hat and a clap. What we can then do is when the track’s playing we can press one of these buttons and it will instantly jump to that point in the track.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:01:02.000
When you do set these The R1 will save them.  If you use CDs it will save them to the R1’s memory and it will save 3 per CD for up to 1000 CDs. The rekordbox USB key that I’m using will automatically save hot cues for up to 3 per track for any of the tracks you’ve got on there.

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:22.000
Once you’ve got these hot cue points saved we can recall them later so I’ll load the same track on to this deck here and once that’s loaded in just press the call button and then the three cue points will flash, just press each one of those to load it in. Exactly the same as it was here; I’ve got a kick a high hat and a clap.

00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:43.000
If you want to change them, or just re record it if it’s a bit wrong, just hold down shift and then touch the cue point you want to delete. If I want to delete A the light then turns off and I can either just hit the button again to re record it or I can scrub through the track and find the exact point that I want.

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:53.000
So that’s all been set there.
