00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:19.000
So if I click on devices, when my USB key shows up just right click and click update collection. It will then bring those cue points back in so just to prove that we’ll go into collection, load the track up and then you can see the cue points are there.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:38.000
We can then use rekordbox as well to recreate those cue points. I can press the ‘X’ button in the hot cue section just here to delete them and you’ll see them deleted from the waveform up here. I can re record them in the exact same way, just as the tracks playing press A, B or C and the shortcut for that as well is function 1, function 2 and function 3.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:47.000
You can re record it or I can scrub through the track manually or I can use the cursor keys to get really accurate if I want as well. Then just press the hot cue buttons.

00:02:49.000 --> 00:03:02.000
Once it has been recorded if I re export that track back to the USB key I can then take that USB and plug it into the R1. Go back into devices and click eject. 

